      Product Description

      MoesGo Smart Light Switch

      This new designed push button wireless smart switch is ideal for replacing traditional switches, offering a new level of convenience and control. It has upgraded features including multi-control association to other smart switches via the Smart Life/Tuya App, together with optional light mode and restart status. You can simply connect the switch via Bluetooth and wifi.

      Package Listing

      • 4* MoesGo Smart Light Switch
      • 1* 4 Gang Switch Plate
      • 1* Quick Installation Guide
      • 1* Bag Install Accessories

      Main Specifications

      • Working voltage: 100-240V AC, 50/60Hz
      • Current type: 15A Max.
      • Wireless type: Wi-Fi 2.4GHz
      • Capacitive load: 1200W/Gang
      • Support system: Android/iOS

      Timer Function

      • Set 1-60 minute countdowns to turn on/off the light via your smartphone, or programme schedules to suit your own timetable.

      Group Control

      • Use one smartphone to control multiple switches or multiple phones to control one switch.
      • Create groups within the app to control all the lights in your home and share control with family members.

      Note

      • Neutral wire is required in your switch boxes to operate correctly.
      • Only supports 2.4G network.
      • Can be used as single pole or mutil-control switch.

      Multiple Non-interfering Control Modes

      Hands-free Voice Control

      • Effortless hands-free control via Amazon Alexa and Google Home.

      Smart Life/Tuya App Remote Control

      • Remotely control your switch wherever you are.

      Manual Control

      • High sensitiyity to simple touch.

      Mutil-control Association

      • Now multi-control association to other smart switches is added into the Smart Life/Tuya App.

      How to achieve multi-control association in Smart Life App ?

      4 out of 5 stars
      Easy Install
      I was concerned the four switches would be a tight fit, but no problem fit just fine.Tip 1: Add neutral (white wire) pigtails to the neutrals all tied together in your switch box. I used 1 pigtail for 2 switches and 1 pigtail on the other 2 switches. FYI a pigtail is an extra wire added to the wires already connected inside your junction box.Tip 2: There are 2 wires connected to your existing switches. Determine which wire is the power wire. You must hook this wire to each of the black wires marked Line on the new switch.The brown marked load,controls the light or appliance.To do this turn off power and pull switches out of the wall box. Turn power back on and test each switch for the power wire. Then turn power off again.Tip 3: Before you install the switches take one of the old screws off one of the old switches and screw this into the new light switch where the cover plate will be fastened. This will make it easier to add the wall cover once you have installed the switches in the wall as thease holes are not threaded from the factory.I installed these swithes for light control schedules on my Alexa app and they work flawlessly. Outside lights turn on at sunset and turn off at sunrise etc.Great product, simple install, I would recommend.

      • Jesse Tilden
        5.0 out of 5 stars Great product; I've bought more since this one.
        Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2023
        Style: 1 Gang White Smart SwitchVerified Purchase
        I was initially skeptical of this product, since it is SO much cheaper than those available at my local hardware stores. After buying and installing this one, however, I've bought the "three gang" model and am about to order several more.

        First, the build quality is great. It looks like a much more expensive switch and I was not at all worried about breaking it during the install.

        Second, the install itself was a piece of cake. If you've ever swapped out a standard light switch or receptacle, the process is exactly the same. It comes with all the wire nuts you will need for the process and a reasonably clear set of instructions. It does require a neutral wire, which most homes of relatively recent vintage support (my house was built in the early 80s, and it had a neutral wire). If you are not sure if you have a neutral wire, just look behind your current switch for a white wire (or wires, if you're working with a 2, 3 or 4 gang) that may or may not be connected to your existing, traditional switch (mine weren't.) If you see one, you are probably good to go.

        Third, Google Home integration was totally seamless. The switch popped right up in the app and works flawlessly from there.

        This is, in sum, a great product and I will continue to buy more of them. Highly recommended!

        4.0 out of 5 stars Great Product, but make sure you have the space behind your switch for the wires!
        Reviewed in the United States on March 1, 2025
        Style: 3 Gang White Smart SwitchVerified Purchase
        Just installed these and they worked great! Connection was easy, and the tactile click of the switch was a nice change from the glass faced touch ones I had before.

        The Only Issue: I installed this in a 3-Gang switch plate. I don't know if you have ever been behind one of those, but it can be a mess of wires. The connections on these switches are not the kind you insert and tighten a screw to secure. You are provided wire nuts and there is solder at the top of each wire to connect them. The lack of space behind the switch is so limiting that the switch itself barely fits, let alone 12 additional wire nuts! I ended up having to twist them together and use heat shrink wire connectors. That is literally my only complaint about these!

      • ER in MA
        5.0 out of 5 stars MoesGo WiFi works as expected
        Reviewed in the United States on August 22, 2022
        Style: 1 Gang White Smart SwitchVerified Purchase
        I added 2 MoesGO single pole switches to an existing 4 gang switch outlet to control my outside lights. I was concerned about fit since it's a tight set up so partially picked these switches based on their rather slim dimensions. It was still tight but the Installation was pretty straight forward it just took some patience. I'm sure if just installing in a single switch box it would have been faster. One thing to note is you will need to make sure you connect the neutral wire since most standard light switches just have power, common and ground. Once installed and powered on I used the SmartLife app and it discovered the two switches right away and I was able to set up fairly easily without issues. You will need to log into your wifi network to enable. You can also link to Google Assistant or Alexa. I use Google Assistant which also linked up but took a bit of going between apps to get to work. Also the SmartLife app itself allows you to program times you want to turn on and off. The only feature I wish they had was a smart setting that would automatically turn on at sunset and off at sunrise. Some other switches I've seen do have this. This will save having to modify settings seasonally. Outside of that one small nit these switches otherwise worked as advertised.
